# Watch Project Rules

This project uses Tailwind CSS instead of MUI.
DO NOT use MUI for components inside apps/watch/src/components/

### Code Implementation Guidelines

- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling instead of MUI components
- Use standard HTML elements with Tailwind classes
- For styling, prioritize Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS
- Follow Tailwind's responsive design patterns using breakpoint prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, etc.)

### Example
Instead of:
```jsx
<Box sx={{ p: 2 }}>
  <Typography variant="h4">Title</Typography>
  <Button variant="contained">Click me</Button>
</Box>
```

Use:
```jsx
<div className="p-4">
  <h4 className="text-2xl font-medium">Title</h4>
  <button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">Click me</button>
</div>
```

All other project guidelines regarding TypeScript best practices, accessibility, naming conventions, etc. should still be followed.
